<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kendra Wilkinson was seen shopping by herself on Tuesday afternoon in Los Angeles. </p>

<p>The 35-year-old reality TV star turned real estate agent was dressed casually with her long and light hair worn down as she donned a beige mask with no makeup on.</p>

<p>This comes after a source told UsWeekly that the former Playboy cover girl is getting along better with her ex-husband Hank Baskett.</p>

<p>Happy lady: Kendra Wilkinson looked to be in good spirits as she left Vons supermarket in Los Angeles with two stuffed plastic bags on Tuesday</p>

<p>Kendra looked to be in good spirits as she left Vons supermarket in Los Angeles with two stuffed plastic bags.</p>

<p>The lingerie model had on a white V-neck, short-sleeved shirt, form-fitting bell-bottom blue denim jeans and white sandals.</p>

<p>The TV vet's hair had an ombre hue with darker roots and lighter ends, but that may be because she has not visited a hair salon since COVID-19 put people on lockdown.</p>

<p>No glam: The lingerie model had on a white V-neck, short-sleeved shirt, form-fitting bell-bottom blue denim jeans and white sandals</p>

<p>New career: The curvy wonder recently announced that she had passed her real estate exam in June and was going to be working with The Agency - a luxury LA firm run by RHOBH Kyle Richards' husband Mauricio Umansky</p>

<p>Earlier this week it was claimed the beauty and her former football player spouse have found new footing as co-parents after officially divorcing in February 2019. </p>

<p>'Kendra and Hank have been very cordial and are in a really good spot with coparenting,' a source told Us Weekly magazine.</p>

<p>'Hank is out of the picture in terms of a romantic relationship, but they have a good thing going when it comes to the kids. They switch off week to week with them.' </p>

<p>On top: Wilkinson, 35, and her ex-husband Hank Baskett, 37, are reportedly in 'a really good  spot' and 'co-parenting effectively' after divorcing two years ago in February 2019; pictured at WE TV celebration in March 2016</p>

<p>The Playboy cover girl and the 37-year-old athlete first met in 2007 when she was filming E!'s The Girls Next Door. </p>

<p>The pair hit it off and wed at the Playboy mansion in 2009 before eventually having two children together, 10-year-old Hank IV and six-year-old Alijah.</p>

<p>Though they had a 10-plus year relationship, they endured rocky patches as seen on the spinoff show Kendra On Top. </p>

<p>The former couple have spent over two years apart, they are said to be 'very cordial' with each other, and are co-parenting effectively. </p>

<p>Family dynamic: Although the former couple have spent over two years apart, they are said to be 'very cordial' with each other, and are co-parenting effectively as is evident on social media</p>

<p>Young love: Kendra and Hank first met in 2007 when she was filming E!'s The Girls Next Door. The pair hit it off and wed at the playboy mansion in 2009 before eventually having two children together, 10-year-old Hank IV and six-year-old Alijah.</p>

<p>This is evident as both Kendra and Hank's social media show them spending lots of time with their two children in a number of different capacities. </p>

<p>From sports games, to boat outings, to family dinners with their grandparents both of them seem to be doing a phenomenal job being stellar parents. </p>

<p>When it comes to romance, the insider claimed Kendra is still single following her split from Hank, though she was briefly linked to DJ Friese at one point and was spotted with a mystery man in Los Angeles during another.  </p>

<p>'Myself and kids are all that matter still and a few great friends. Anything more than that I haven't confirmed...healing is still in progress' she wrote to her followers when confronted with public speculation of dating rumors. </p>

<p>Focus on the kids: The newly single mother said at the time she found it 'scary' to think about 'trusting' someone again, though she did believe she would find her 'soulmate' one day; October 2019 at a Chargers game</p>

<p> The single mother said at the time she found it 'scary' to think about 'trusting' someone again, though she did believe she would find her 'soulmate' one day.  </p>

<p>'I try to just go with the flow and do what makes me happy and what makes my soul smile,' Wilkinson said. </p>

<p>The former reality star recently embarked on a new career path while in quarantine, announcing back in June that she had passed her real estate exam. </p>

<p>Shortly thereafter, Wilkinson revealed that she would be going to work at The Agency - the luxury real estate firm run by Real Housewives of Beverly Hills star, Kyle Richard's husband Mauricio Umansky.  </p>

<p>'I do believe in love and I do believe I will in time find my soulmate but for now mama is just having fun exploring my new life. I'm healthy and kids are great and for now that still remains top priority' she added. </p>

<p>New chapter: Kendra posted to social media last year to thank her former husband Hank for their years of wedded bliss though she added she was 'sad and heartbroken' also adding that there was no hate in their marriage</p>
